 "You're here. Good...there's a lot to get done before we can go into the field," said JFK as he pointed to an array of weapons on the table." JFK said. His guard, Reggie, was nearby to ensure that he wouldn't be discovered. Nodding to Reggie as he exited his house, Barack said, "I'll see you in a couple days."
Hours later, Barack arrived at the secret JFK compound.
 "You're here. Good...there's a lot to get done before we can go into the field," said JFK as he pointed to an array of weapons on the table." JFK said. Bill Clinton and the other presidents stood quietly. They know what JFK is talking about. "We, the lizardmen are here to wipe out the human race."
